SIMPLE: inattentive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inattentive
<hw>In`at*ten"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>inattentif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not attentive; not fixing the mind on
an object; heedless; careless; negligent; regardless; <as>as, an
<ex>inattentive</ex> spectator or hearer; an <ex>inattentive</ex>
habit.</as></def> <rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Careless; heedless; regardless; thoughtless;
negligent; remiss; inadvertent.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In`at*ten"tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In`at*ten"tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inaudibility</ent>⟦br⟧
